# 📋 Docker Commands Practiced

## Check Docker Version

```bash
docker --version
```

Example

```
Docker version 29.x.x
```

---

## Detailed Docker Information

```bash
docker info
```

This command displays two sections.

### Client Information

- Docker CLI Version
- Plugins
- Context
- Debug Status

### Server Information

- Docker Engine Version
- Storage Driver
- Running Containers
- Images
- CPU
- Memory
- Docker Root Directory
- Operating System

---

## List Images

```bash
docker images
```

or

```bash
docker image ls
```

Both commands produce the same output.

---

## Running Containers

```bash
docker ps
```

Displays only running containers.

---

## All Containers

```bash
docker ps -a
